Description: Use SONAME-versioned library name for dlopen
 The Debian libcoraza1 package ships the shared library with a
 versioned SONAME (libcoraza.so.1). The bare libcoraza.so symlink
 is only in the -dev package. Adjust the dlopen extension to use
 the SONAME major version.
Author: Pierre Pomes <pierre.pomes@gmail.com>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-03-18
---
--- a/src/dynlib.h
+++ b/src/dynlib.h
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@
 #ifdef __APPLE__
 #define DYNLIB_EXT ".dylib"
 #else
-#define DYNLIB_EXT ".so"
+#define DYNLIB_EXT ".so.1"
 #endif

 static inline dynlib_t dynlib_open(const char *path)
